# Setup

1. Clone the repo:
   git clone https://github.com/Mrdqrk/HangMan-AppClass.git
   cd HangMan-AppClass

2. Install dependencies:
   pip install -r requirements.txt

3. Paste To terminal 
export SUPABASE_URL="https://jaduiuxggmwxftpltvvh.supabase.co/"
export SUPABASE_KEY="eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6ImphZHVpdXhnZ213eGZ0cGx0dnZoIiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3NTk4ODcwODAsImV4cCI6MjA3NTQ2MzA4MH0.eSph4F9e8K6c5lwRpGAYZYZDOdKP-uCUoaFWidaoF-8"


4. Run Main.py 


# HangVersus (EXE Launch)

1. Run the game
   Double-click HangVersus.exe
   If Windows warns you, click More info â†’ Run anyway

2. Required files (same folder as .exe)

   HangVersus.exe
   images/
     background.png
     bgPlay.jpg
     images/
       cowboys/
       pixar/
       social/
   sounds/
     duel.mp3
     good.mp3
     win.mp3
     lost.mp3
   character_offsets.json
   .env

3. Supabase mode (online)
   Open the .env file next to the .exe
   Make sure it contains:
$env:SUPABASE_URL="https://jaduiuxggmwxftpltvvh.supabase.co/"
$env:SUPABASE_KEY="eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI6IkpXVCJ9.eyJpc3MiOiJzdXBhYmFzZSIsInJlZiI6ImphZHVpdXhnZ213eGZ0cGx0dnZoIiwicm9sZSI6ImFub24iLCJpYXQiOjE3NTk4ODcwODAsImV4cCI6MjA3NTQ2MzA4MH0.eSph4F9e8K6c5lwRpGAYZYZDOdKP-uCUoaFWidaoF-8"

4. Offline mode
   If .env is missing or Supabase is unreachable:
   - Game runs in offline mode
   - Default/local phrases are used
   - Scores and leaderboards are disabled
   - Gameplay still works normally

5. If the game closes instantly
   1. Do not run from a .zip file
   2. Put the .exe in a normal folder (example: Desktop\HangVersus\)
   3. Make sure images/ and sounds/ folders are beside the .exe
   4. Make sure character_offsets.json is present
   5. To see errors:
      - Open Command Prompt
      - cd into the folder with the .exe
      - run: HangVersus.exe

6. Controls
   1. Type one letter and press Enter (or click Guess Letter)
   2. Click Guess Phrase to attempt the full phrase
   3. Turn banner shows:
      YOUR TURN
      BOT'S TURN

7. Notes
   - README edits do NOT require rebuilding the .exe
   - Only code or asset changes require rebuilding
   - Offline mode is intended for demos and testing
